'''5uper.net''' was an international artist group based in Austria that focused on artistic research at the intersection of media, arts, technology and society.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:5CxkaKj_VFMJ:https://5uper.net/page/about.html+&cd=2&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=at |title=About |publisher=5uper.net |accessdate=13 April 2017}}</ref> The group was established in 2003 by Ile Cvetkoski, Matthias Tarasiewicz, Karina Lackner and Michal Wlodkowski<ref>{{cite web|title=WHOisWHO |publisher=5uper.net |url=http://5uper.net/page/about |accessdate=18 April 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060203212950/http://5uper.net/page/about |archivedate=3 February 2006 }}</ref> and was responsible for developing the [[Coded Cultures]] festival series.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Reiter|first1=Teresa|title=Bestandsaufnahmen der Medienkunst|url=https://thegap.at/bestandsaufnahmen-der-medienkunst/|accessdate=18 April 2017|work=The Gap|date=7 September 2011}}</ref>
