'''Adele Lim''' is a TV and movie screenwriter.
== Early life == Lim was born in Malaysia. <ref name="IMDb">{{cit web |URL=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1004604/ |title=Adele Lim |publisher=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref> Lim is of Malaysian Chinese descent. <ref name="awardsdaily"/>. She attended Malaysia's prestigious Sri Aman Girls School.
== Career == Lim started her Hollywood career in [[Xena: Warrior Princess]]. <ref name="awardsdaily"/> Lim is known for her writing on TV shows such as [[One Tree Hill (TV series)|One Tree Hill]], [[Life Unexpected]], [[Reign]] and [[Star-Crossed (TV series)|Star-Crossed]]. In 2018, Lim was co-screenwriter for the 2018 movie ''[[Crazy Rich Asians (film)]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-crazy-rich-asians-adele-lim-20180810-story.html|title='Crazy Rich Asians': Adele Lim brought experience, authenticity to the script|last=Yamato|first=Jen|website=latimes.com|date=August 10, 2018|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref> <ref name="awardsdaily">{{cit web |URL=http://www.awardsdaily.com/2018/08/19/adele-lim-representation-matters-says-the-malaysian-co-writer-of-crazy-rich-asians/ |title=Adele Lim "Representation Matters" Says the Malaysian Co-Writer of Crazy Rich aasisans |publisher=awardsdaily.com |last=Tangcay |first=Jazz|date=August 21, 2018|accessdate=August 29, 2018}}</ref>
