{{other uses}} {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} In [[sewing]] and [[handicraft|crafts]] an '''embellishment''' is anything that adds design interest to the piece.
==A few common examples of embellishment in sewing and craft== * [[applique|appliqué]] can be made by sewing machine of decorative techniques and or * [[embroidery]], done either by machine or by hand * [[piping (sewing)|piping]] made from either [[self-fabric]], [[contrast fabric]], or a simply a cord. * [[trim (sewing)]] * [[lace]], either pre-made or [[tatting|home-made]] * [[Fringe (trim)]] * [[bead]]s * [[batik]]
Items that normally serve a function may also be used as embellishment. For example: * [[button]]s can be placed anywhere on the piece * [[zipper]]s can be unzipped and be used as piping, or simply stitched on * [[buckle]]s can be placed anywhere on the piece * [[grommet]]s can be placed anywhere even when there is no cord is looped through them * [[sequin]]s can be placed anywhere
